    • importFromCSV

      public static void importFromCSV​(java.io.File file) throws java.io.FileNotFoundException, java.io.IOException
      Imports the dictionary of IUCR codes from a CSV file. The CSV file is of the same format as provided here. That is, it has four columns, iucr, primary description, secondary description, and index code, in that order. The first line (the header line) is skipped.
      Parameters:
      file - The CSV file from which to import the dictionary of IUCR codes.
      Throws:
      java.io.FileNotFoundException - If the no file was found at the specified file path.
      java.io.IOException - If an error occurs whilst trying to read the IUCR codes from the file.

    • getPrimaryDescription

      public static java.lang.String getPrimaryDescription​(java.lang.String iucr)
      Returns the primary description associated with a particular IUCR code.
      Parameters:
      iucr - The IUCR code as a string, used as a key to find the IUCRCodeStruct object in the dictionary.
      Returns:
      The primary description associated with the iucr code.
      Throws:
      java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the IUCR does not exist within the dictionary.
